	<entry>
		<title>Welcome to Quake2Lithium.com!</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://quake2lithium.com/component/content/article/47-welcome-to-quake2lithiumcom"/>
		<published>2100-05-22T12:11:12Z</published>
		<updated>2100-05-22T12:11:12Z</updated>
		<id>https://quake2lithium.com/component/content/article/47-welcome-to-quake2lithiumcom</id>
		<author>
			<name>Administrator</name>
		<email>admin@quake2lithium.com</email>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Quake2Lithium.com is a fansite and international community dedicated to preserving the legacy of Lithium.&amp;nbsp; Lithium is a server-side modification for Quake 2 created by Matt &quot;WhiteFang&quot; Ayres and released as open source in January 2010.&amp;nbsp; Quake 2 Lithium is easily one of the fastest first person shooters ever released with unique gameplay including an off-hand grappling hook and runes (power-ups).&amp;nbsp; See the action for yourself!&amp;nbsp; Ready to play? Read our &lt;a target=&quot;_self&quot; href=&quot;https://quake2lithium.com/index.php?option=com_content&amp;amp;view=article&amp;amp;id=48&amp;amp;Itemid=71&quot;&gt;Quick Start Guide&lt;/a&gt; and with a FREE download, you're all set to frag!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;{jumi [*11]}&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Quake2Lithium.com is a fansite and international community dedicated to preserving the legacy of Lithium.&amp;nbsp; Lithium is a server-side modification for Quake 2 created by Matt &quot;WhiteFang&quot; Ayres and released as open source in January 2010.&amp;nbsp; Quake 2 Lithium is easily one of the fastest first person shooters ever released with unique gameplay including an off-hand grappling hook and runes (power-ups).&amp;nbsp; See the action for yourself!&amp;nbsp; Ready to play? Read our &lt;a target=&quot;_self&quot; href=&quot;https://quake2lithium.com/index.php?option=com_content&amp;amp;view=article&amp;amp;id=48&amp;amp;Itemid=71&quot;&gt;Quick Start Guide&lt;/a&gt; and with a FREE download, you're all set to frag!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;{jumi [*11]}&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
	</entry>
	<entry>
		<title>All good things...</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://quake2lithium.com/component/content/article/1-latest-news/84-all-good-things"/>
		<published>2018-04-02T15:55:34Z</published>
		<updated>2018-04-02T15:55:34Z</updated>
		<id>https://quake2lithium.com/component/content/article/1-latest-news/84-all-good-things</id>
		<author>
			<name>Administrator</name>
		<email>admin@quake2lithium.com</email>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Nothing lasts forever, but Q2 and Lithium will live on in the hearts and minds of all that have played throughout the years.&amp;nbsp; Though this will be the final update to this site, it will live on for archival purposes and migrated over to github in a static form.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A static form of this site will be accessible @ &lt;a href=&quot;https://quake2lithium.github.io&quot;&gt;https://quake2lithium.github.io&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Forum has been disabled permanently to support hosting on github.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All downloads on this site will live-on and be made available through github.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Nothing lasts forever, but Q2 and Lithium will live on in the hearts and minds of all that have played throughout the years.&amp;nbsp; Though this will be the final update to this site, it will live on for archival purposes and migrated over to github in a static form.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A static form of this site will be accessible @ &lt;a href=&quot;https://quake2lithium.github.io&quot;&gt;https://quake2lithium.github.io&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Forum has been disabled permanently to support hosting on github.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;All downloads on this site will live-on and be made available through github.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</content>
	</entry>
	<entry>
		<title>Lithium II v1.31 released!</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://quake2lithium.com/component/content/article/1-latest-news/80-lithium-ii-v131-released"/>
		<published>2010-09-19T00:00:00Z</published>
		<updated>2010-09-19T00:00:00Z</updated>
		<id>https://quake2lithium.com/component/content/article/1-latest-news/80-lithium-ii-v131-released</id>
		<author>
			<name>Administrator</name>
		<email>admin@quake2lithium.com</email>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Matt &quot;WhiteFang&quot; Ayres has released v1.31 of his signature Lithium II Mod focusing on stability and bug fixes!!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Lithium II?&lt;/strong&gt; - Lithium II is a very configurable server-side modification for Quake II which includes deathmatch and CTF modes.&amp;nbsp; Lithium II is well known for it's red-laser style off-hand grappling hook and runes.&amp;nbsp; Have a closer look at the feature list &lt;a href=&quot;http://quake2.lithium.com/features.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Download:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://quake2lithium.com//lithdownloads/viewcategory/5-lithium-mod&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Changelog:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;v1.31 - Sep 2010&lt;br /&gt;----------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;br /&gt;added, &lt;a href=&quot;http://github.com/WhiteFang34/li2mod&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;source repository&lt;/a&gt; to github&lt;br /&gt;fixed, MOTD buffer overflow (from ralf)&lt;br /&gt;added, use strlcpy/strlcat to protect against buffer overflows (from ralf)&lt;br /&gt;thanks, ralf for all of the improvements, cleanup and updates for VC 2010&lt;br /&gt;fixed, runes should be dropped for reuse if player goes into observer mode&lt;br /&gt;added, don't repeat the same map if it was just voted on&lt;br /&gt;added, time left to top of CTF scoreboard&lt;br /&gt;fixed, rune spawning was broken if resist rune was disabled&lt;br /&gt;fixed, safety couldn't be disabled by setting use_safety to 0&lt;br /&gt;fixed, consistency of regen rune timing&lt;br /&gt;fixed, chasecam mode didn't work if CTF was enabled&lt;br /&gt;fixed, CTF flag was dropped from observers at level start&lt;br /&gt;added, CTF flag return sound when it's returned for timeout&lt;br /&gt;fixed, force CTF team menu after going into observer, chasecam or next map&lt;br /&gt;added, muzzle logic to say_team command&lt;br /&gt;disabled, lmaster support for now (and removed from docs)&lt;br /&gt;thanks, again to d3s for facilitating this release!&lt;/p&gt;</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Matt &quot;WhiteFang&quot; Ayres has released v1.31 of his signature Lithium II Mod focusing on stability and bug fixes!!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Lithium II?&lt;/strong&gt; - Lithium II is a very configurable server-side modification for Quake II which includes deathmatch and CTF modes.&amp;nbsp; Lithium II is well known for it's red-laser style off-hand grappling hook and runes.&amp;nbsp; Have a closer look at the feature list &lt;a href=&quot;http://quake2.lithium.com/features.html&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Download:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://quake2lithium.com//lithdownloads/viewcategory/5-lithium-mod&quot; target=&quot;_self&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Changelog:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;v1.31 - Sep 2010&lt;br /&gt;----------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;br /&gt;added, &lt;a href=&quot;http://github.com/WhiteFang34/li2mod&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;source repository&lt;/a&gt; to github&lt;br /&gt;fixed, MOTD buffer overflow (from ralf)&lt;br /&gt;added, use strlcpy/strlcat to protect against buffer overflows (from ralf)&lt;br /&gt;thanks, ralf for all of the improvements, cleanup and updates for VC 2010&lt;br /&gt;fixed, runes should be dropped for reuse if player goes into observer mode&lt;br /&gt;added, don't repeat the same map if it was just voted on&lt;br /&gt;added, time left to top of CTF scoreboard&lt;br /&gt;fixed, rune spawning was broken if resist rune was disabled&lt;br /&gt;fixed, safety couldn't be disabled by setting use_safety to 0&lt;br /&gt;fixed, consistency of regen rune timing&lt;br /&gt;fixed, chasecam mode didn't work if CTF was enabled&lt;br /&gt;fixed, CTF flag was dropped from observers at level start&lt;br /&gt;added, CTF flag return sound when it's returned for timeout&lt;br /&gt;fixed, force CTF team menu after going into observer, chasecam or next map&lt;br /&gt;added, muzzle logic to say_team command&lt;br /&gt;disabled, lmaster support for now (and removed from docs)&lt;br /&gt;thanks, again to d3s for facilitating this release!&lt;/p&gt;</content>
	</entry>
	<entry>
		<title>Official Site Launch!</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://quake2lithium.com/component/content/article/1-latest-news/55-official-site-launch"/>
		<published>2010-07-16T00:00:00Z</published>
		<updated>2010-07-16T00:00:00Z</updated>
		<id>https://quake2lithium.com/component/content/article/1-latest-news/55-official-site-launch</id>
		<author>
			<name>Administrator</name>
		<email>admin@quake2lithium.com</email>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Your one-stop site for everything Lithium related has been launched!&amp;nbsp; We could say in a sense it's been 10+ years in the making, but better late than never! =)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;So, sit back, take your shoes off and take a test drive of our site.&amp;nbsp; Come in and say hello on the forums, stop in our live chat room, and then go and download Quake 2!&amp;nbsp; Don't forget that if you need any help getting started or reacquainted with the game, help is only a click or post away. &lt;/p&gt;</summary>
		<content type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Your one-stop site for everything Lithium related has been launched!&amp;nbsp; We could say in a sense it's been 10+ years in the making, but better late than never! =)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;So, sit back, take your shoes off and take a test drive of our site.&amp;nbsp; Come in and say hello on the forums, stop in our live chat room, and then go and download Quake 2!&amp;nbsp; Don't forget that if you need any help getting started or reacquainted with the game, help is only a click or post away. &lt;/p&gt;</content>
	</entry>
